description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Quality Compliance Support Officer to join the Risk and Patient Safety team. You will need to be self-driven with excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an ability to work at all levels of the organization. You will take pride in your work, be highly motivated, professional, have a flexible approach, good organizational skills, excellent attention to detail and be able to work to deadlines and write reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As post holder you will be responsible for liaising with Directors, Chiefs of Service, Service Directors, Matrons and Nursing Staff, Senior Managers and Corporate Staff in order to assist in producing the Trust’s annual Quality Report in line with statutory requirements, the Norfolk and Norwich NHS Foundation Trust objectives and Quality Improvement strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for facilitating responses to Quality Issue reports, monitoring progress against Trust Quality Priorities and collating analysing and presenting quality, risk and safety information in order to provide clear and accurate reports for the Board, Sub Board committees and groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also support activities related to improving service delivery and quality and to support compliance with regulatory standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of a high quality, safe and compassionate healthcare service, all staff are expected to act as a role model to others in all aspects of their work and consistently demonstrate NNUH’s ‘PRIDE’ values of People focused, Respect, Integrity, Dedication and Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 26th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gemma Lynch - Governance Compliance Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel:&lt;/strong&gt; 01603 647265&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email:&lt;/strong&gt; gemma.lynch@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
